{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:16:49.407349+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my exploration of the repository, here's a summary of the module structure:\n\n---\n\n## Module Structure Summary\n\nThis is a **multi-module Spring Boot Gradle project** (`spring-boot-java-template`) with a layered architecture organized into **5 top-level module groups**, containing **7 submodules** total. It's designed as a good starting template for early-stage projects where developer productivity matters.\n\n### 1. `core/` — Domain & Application Logic\nThe heart of the application. Each submodule represents a domain service area.\n\n- **`core:core-api`** — The **only executable module** (it produces a `bootJar`). It acts as the application entry point, hosts domain logic, exposes REST APIs, and depends on nearly every other module (`core-enum`, `support:logging`, `support:monitoring`, `storage:db-core`, `clients:client-example`). It uses `spring-boot-starter-webmvc`.\n\n- **`core:core-enum`** — A library of **shared enums** used by `core-api` and potentially exposed to external consumers. Contains no runtime logic—just type-safe constants shared across the codebase.\n\n### 2. `clients/` — External System Integration\nModules here encapsulate outbound communication with third-party services.\n\n- **`clients:client-example`** — A reference implementation demonstrating **HTTP client integration via Spring Cloud OpenFeign**. Intended as a pattern for adding more client modules as the project grows.\n\n### 3. `storage/` — Persistence Layer\nHandles database connectivity and data access.\n\n- **`storage:db-core`** — Demonstrates connecting to **MySQL using Spring Data JPA**. Separates the persistence concern from the domain logic in `core-api`.\n\n### 4. `support/` — Cross-Cutting Concerns\nInfrastructure-level support modules that are not domain-specific.\n\n- **`support:logging`** — Provides **structured logging and distributed tracing** support, including Sentry integration for error tracking.\n\n- **`support:monitoring`** — Provides **application monitoring** capabilities (e.g., health checks, metrics via Spring Boot Actuator).\n\n### 5. `tests/` — Testing Utilities\nModules dedicated to making test authoring easier.\n\n- **`tests:api-docs`** — Utilities for generating **API documentation via Spring REST Docs and AsciiDoc**. It's used as a `testImplementation` dependency in `core-api`.\n\n---\n\n### Dependency Flow (simplified)\n\n```\ncore-api (bootJar - the app)\n ├── core-enum\n ├── support:logging\n ├── support:monitoring\n ├── storage:db-core\n ├── clients:client-example\n └── tests:api-docs  (test only)\n```\n\n### Key Design Principles\n\n1. **Separation of concerns** — Storage, client integration, logging, and monitoring are isolated from domain logic.\n2. **Single executable module** — Only `core-api` produces a runnable Spring Boot jar; all other modules are libraries.\n3. **Growth-friendly** — The README explicitly notes that new domains can be added as additional submodules under `core/`, new clients under `clients/`, etc.\n4. **Profile-driven environments** — Supports `local`, `local-dev`, `dev`, `staging`, and `live` profiles.\n5. **Structured testing** — Tests are categorized by tags (`unitTest`, `contextTest`, `restDocsTest`, `developTest`) for selective execution in CI pipelines.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 735, "prompt_tokens": 8637, "total_tokens": 9372, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 11, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8384, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007796874, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001402374, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00063945}}, "m